<HEADLINE>
<P>
REP. STARK'S COMMENTS ABOUT LOUIS SULLIVAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In regards to the remarks of Rep. Stark calling Sullivan "a disgrace to his 
position and to his race": 
</P>
<P>
As a physician, I am familiar with previous derogatory statements by Rep. 
Stark. 
</P>
<P>
One of his favorite ways of referring to doctors is "those bastards." 
</P>
<P>
I submit that Rep. Stark is a real "hater" and that he truly despises anyone 
who fails to support his positions. 
</P>
<P>
I suspect that he is furious that any black would not only disagree with him, 
but would dare to be a physician also. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH L. CLAY, MD 
</P>
<P>
Santa Maria 
</P>
</TEXT>
