<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bring on Van Cliburn: Piano virtuoso Van Cliburn will give his first 
full-length solo recital in more than a decade this October in Kilgore, Tex., 
his boyhood home. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the recital will benefit the Harvey Lavan and Rildia Bee O'Bryan 
Cliburn Scholarship, named for Cliburn's parents, at Kilgore Junior College. 
Cliburn, 56, revived his performing career at the White House in December, 
1987, and has played selections from his solo repertoire at private 
fund-raising events and as encores for his orchestral appearances, but the 
Kilgore event will be his first complete solo recital since 1978. Cliburn also 
will perform this season with the Lincoln, Neb., Symphony on Sept. 21. GREG 
BRAXTON 
</P>
