villages in Sri Lanka. Military officials said Muslims were cut down in the 
streets with machine-gun fire and machetes. The killings were the latest in a 
round of spiraling ethnic violence that pits Tamil separatists against the 
Sinhalese-dominated government in the island nation. In Eravur, one of the 
villages hit in Saturday night's attack, women mourned their lost relatives, 
right. Associated Press 
</P>
