<P>
MAN WOUNDED IN 2ND BART ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man shot and wounded in the second violent confrontation aboard a BART train 
in less than a week was in serious condition, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Spain, 19, of Hayward underwent surgery after being shot in the stomach, 
said Thomas McGarry, a spokesman at Eden Medical Center in Castro Valley. A 
train operator reported loud voices and a fistfight involving six men on the 
northbound train approaching the San Leandro station, BART spokesman Sy Mouber 
said. Spain was shot as the train pulled into the station, Mouber said. The 
incident came only days after the first fatality aboard a BART train. Last 
weekend, Daniel Kirby, 36, was fatally stabbed near Berkeley's Ashby station. 
</P>
