DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN DIES OF HEART ATTACK AFTER CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Canyon Country woman died of a heart attack Sunday afternoon after losing 
control of her car while suffering chest pains, Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The 60-year-old woman, whose name was not released pending notification of her 
relatives, was driving south on Sand Canyon Road in Santa Clarita about 1:45 
p.m. when her car ran off the road and crashed into a ditch, said Sgt. Steve 
Jenkins. 
</P>
<P>
The woman told deputies who arrived after the accident that her chest pains 
made it impossible for her to control her car, Jenkins said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was rushed by ambulance to Henry Mayo Newhall Hospital, where she 
died at 3 p.m. of a heart attack, a hospital spokeswoman said. The victim had a 
history of heart trouble, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
