<TEXT>
<P>
Darius (Doc) Young, a U.S. citizen residing in Alberta, Canada, won an Olympic 
slot for the United States at the world shooting championships in Moscow. 
</P>
<P>
Young got 579 out of a possible 600 points in the men's air pistol event to 
finish eighth. The U.S. now has a reserved position in the men's air-pistol 
event at the 1992 Olympic Games in Barcelona. 
</P>
