<P>
BALBOA ISLAND PARK PLAN TO BE STUDIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Council members today will consider a proposal to turn the site of a 
former gas station at Marine and Park avenues into a mini-park for residents of 
Balboa Island, Little Island and Collins Island. 
</P>
<P>
The Unocal station has already been demolished, and the city has budgeted money 
to buy the site and build a fire station on the major portion of the land, 
which sits at the southeastern corner of the intersection. 
</P>
<P>
The fire station plans have been put on hold, however, because area homeowner 
associations have expressed interest in building and maintaining a small park 
at the location. Their urgings prompted City Manager Robert L. Wynn to devise a 
proposal calling for the city to finance the demolition and then build a 
mini-park. 
</P>
<P>
Council members will not take any action on the issue. 
