<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; 
</P>
<P>
CITY COUNCIL TO AID ANTI-DRUG EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Council members voted last week to spend $500 on Red Ribbon Week, an 
October event that officials said will help demonstrate the city's commitment 
to fighting drug and alcohol abuse. 
</P>
<P>
In the past, local organizations and schools have conducted their own programs. 
This year, however, Mayor Eva G. Miner suggested a coordinated approach to the 
community activities, and the council agreed. The week of Oct. 21-28 has been 
set aside for the event. 
</P>
<P>
City officials will encourage local schools and community organizations to 
participate in the activities and will try to inform residents of the schedule 
of events. The city's contribution will go toward distributing buttons, ribbons 
and balloons, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
