<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
CHASE OFFERS RETIREMENT LURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chase Manhattan Corp. is offering severance to longtime U.S. employees as part 
of a previously announced effort to trim costs and staff, a spokesman for the 
nation's second-biggest banking company said today. 
</P>
<P>
The banking company last week offered employees who retire with at least 10 
years service two week's pay for every year of service; those with at least 20 
years would get three weeks' pay for every year of service. 
</P>
<P>
A company spokesman was unable to say how many of the company's 30,000 domestic 
employees are eligible for the program but estimated that it is a few thousand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
