<P>
'BONFIRE' COMPLETES FILMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Bonfire of the Vanities," a Warner Bros. drama based on Tom Wolfe's 
best-selling novel, completed principal photography in Hollywood after 16 weeks 
of production. 
</P>
<P>
Produced and directed by Brian De Palma, "The Bonfire of the Vanities" stars 
Tom Hanks, Bruce Willis, Melanie Griffith and Morgan Freeman. The supporting 
cast includes F. Murray Abraham, Kim Cattrall, Saul Rubinek and John Hancock. 
</P>
<P>
The movie, due for release at the end of the year, was filmed in four New York 
boroughs and in sections of New Jersey. 
</P>
