<P>
CABLE STAR LEAVES AWARD RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lucy Webb, star of "Not Necessarily The News" on cable TV, has withdrawn from 
consideration as a comic actress nominee in this year's Academy of Cable 
Excellence awards, her publicist said. 
</P>
<P>
Webb has won the ACE award for "Best Actress in a Comedy Series" for the past 
five years, and wants to give others a chance, publicist Monique Moss said. 
</P>
<P>
"I've been overwhelmed by the Academy's generous acknowledgement of my work on 
'NNTN,' ' Webb said. "It's meant more to me than I can say, but there comes a 
time when you have to pass the baton." 
</P>
<P>
Webb has been working on an HBO special tentatively scheduled for late 1990. 
The untitled show was created and co-written by Webb and Dava Savel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
