THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
KOREA WILD ABOUT ASIAN GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL, South Korea 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There are so many people who want to visit China for the Asian Games next month 
that a computer will decide who gets to go, officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
Those who are chosen will be required to watch at least one game and root for 
South Korean athletes, said authorities at the Transportation Ministry. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly 50,000 people, about 12 times the number authorized, have applied to 
visit China as tourists during the Sept. 22-Oct. 7 games in Beijing. A computer 
will be used to choose names at random. 
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors is being restricted because of limited transportation 
services and accommodations in Beijing. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the tourists, South Korea will have about 1,500 athletes, 
officials and reporters in Beijing during the games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
