<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVIS CUP SEMIFINALS TEAM NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andre Agassi, Michael Chang, Rick Leach and Jim Pugh will represent the United 
States against Austria in the Davis Cup semifinals next month, the U.S. Tennis 
Assn. announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Agassi, 7-2 in Davis Cup singles, is ranked fourth in the world. Chang, ranked 
10th, is 2-0 in the Davis Cup with both victories coming against Paraguay last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
Leach and Pugh beat Mexico in the opening round of this year's Davis Cup. Pugh 
is ranked first in doubles and Leach is fourth. 
</P>
<P>
The winner of the series, to be played Sept. 21-23 in Vienna, plays the winner 
of the series between Argentina and Australia. The Americans will be the host 
for the finals if they advance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
